Sverchok parametric tools 0.2.7
addon for: blender.org
License: GPL3

Sverchok - is parametsic tool for architect, allowing to programm geometry in non-text mode, with nodes. 
Mesh programming, operates with separate coordinates, vectors (the sama as vectors in sverchok with base always zero),
rotation angles, matrices (user-freandly rotation-scale-location).
Many tools (>50 nodes 0.2.7v).
You may make with sverchok: parametric constructions, calculate areas, materials, 
change parameters, that you programmed easily, vector fields, cross sections etc etc etc.


Install as blender addon, ctrl+alt+U => addons => install from file => choose zip-archive => activate flag => 
=> open node area in window (change window area type)


Homepage http://nikitron.cc.ua/sverchok.html


Authors: Alexander Nedovizin, Nikita Gorodetskiy, Linus Yng, Agustin Gimenez
